quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  39,42,"It is Allah Who recalls the souls of men upon their death, and of the living during their sleep. He withholds the souls of those on whom He has passed the decree of death, and restores the rest till an appointed term. Surely there are signs in this for those who think"
  39,43,"Have they taken others besides Allah to intercede for them? Ask them: \"How can they intercede, if they have neither control over anything nor do they understand"
  39,44,"Say: \"Intercession is wholly in the hands of Allah. To Him belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth, and to Him you shall all be brought back"
  39,45,"When Allah’s Oneness is mentioned, the hearts of those who deny the hereafter shrink with aversion; but when other gods are mentioned, they are filled with joy"
  39,46,"Pray: \"O Allah! Creator of the heavens and the earth, Who has the knowledge of the unseen and the seen! You Alone can judge the disputes of your servants concerning those matters in which they differ"
  39,47,"If the wrongdoers possessed all the treasures of the earth and as much more besides it, they would gladly offer it to redeem themselves from the painful punishment on the Day of Resurrection. For Allah will show them what they would have never imagined"
  39,48,The evil result of their deeds will become manifest to them and they will be completely encircled by the very thing they used to mock at
  39,49,"Man is such that when he is in trouble he appeals to Us; but when We bestow Our favor upon him, he says: \"This has been given to me because of certain knowledge I possess.\" Nay! It is but a test, yet most of them do not know"
  39,50,"The same was said by those who passed before them, but they gained nothing from what they did"
  39,51,"and the evil consequences of their deeds overtook them. Very soon, the wrongdoers among these people will also be overtaken by the evil consequences of their misdeeds and they will not be able to escape"
  39,52,Do they not know that Allah enlarges the provision for whom He pleases and restricts it from whom He wills? Surely there are signs in this for those who believe